ock.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20that%20constant%20state%20of%20alertness%20began%20to%20take%20its%20toll.%20%E2%80%9CAfter%20being%20an%20adult%20too%20early%20in%20life%2C%20I%20once%20believed%20that%20I%20never%20wanted%20a%20family%2C%20fearing%20the%20load%20of%20responsibilities%20it%20comes%20with%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CSomewhere%20along%20the%20way%2C%20I%20learnt%20to%20be%20the%20adult%20in%20every%20room%2C%20to%20fix%20things%20before%20anyone%20asked.%20And%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20always%20solving%20other%20people%E2%80%99s%20problems%2C%20you%20stop%20letting%20yourself%20feel%20your%20own.%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20scared%20me%20most%20about%20the%20idea%20of%20having%20a%20family%20%E2%80%94%20what%20if%20I%20disappeared%20into%20it%20too%3F%20And%20more%20importantly%2C%20what%20if%20I%20was%20just%20too%20burnt%20out%20to%20do%20it%20justice%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Choosing%20myself%20was%20tough%2C%20but%20important%E2%80%99%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELife%20had%20other%20plans%20for%20her%2C%20and%20her%20husband%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20her%20biggest%20support%20system.%20With%20that%20new%20foundation%20in%20place%2C%20Mahira%20began%20to%20rediscover%20herself.%20When%20Naina%20relapsed%20years%20later%2C%20Mahira%20was%20struggling%20with%20her%20own%20mental%20health%20and%20had%20a%20new%20family%20to%20care%20for%2C%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20sister%20and%20I%20have%20been%20best%20friends%2C%20always%20doing%20things%20together%20and%20talking%20to%20each%20other%20about%20everything.%20But%20the%20dynamic%20has%20always%20been%20one%20where%20I%E2%80%99m%20the%20solution%20provider%2C%20the%20one%20who%20always%20compromises.%20It%20was%20very%20natural%20for%20me%20to%20be%20that%20person%2C%20and%20I%20never%20questioned%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20Mahira%20adds%2C%20their%20dynamic%20was%20challenged%20because%20she%20had%20her%20own%20responsibilities%20to%20take%20care%20of%2C%20and%20Naina%E2%80%99s%20condition%20still%20expected%20the%20same%20kind%20of%20support.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20still%20carries%20a%20hint%20of%20that%20frustration%2C%20of%20having%20been%20put%20in%20a%20position%20to%20show%20up%20for%20other%20people%E2%80%99s%20problems%20by%20discarding%20her%20own%2C%20for%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBridging%20the%20gaps%20with%20care%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMahira%E2%80%99s%20story%20echoes%20what%20thousands%20face%20in%20India%20every%20day.%20While%20private%20care%20options%20exist%2C%20they%20are%20often%20unaffordable.%20Public%20hospitals%2C%20though%20well-intentioned%2C%20are%20overstretched.%20Families%20wait%20hours%2C%20sometimes%20days%2C%20to%20see%20a%20psychiatrist.%20And%20after%20a%20patient%20receives%20critical%20care%20and%20is%20sent%20home%2C%20there%20are%20barely%20any%20active%20communities%20or%20public%20forums%20for%20caregivers%20to%20turn%20to%2C%20leaving%20them%20to%20manage%20the%20emotional%20and%20logistical%20load%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDr%20Shaji%20shares%2C%20%E2%80%9CSchizophrenia%20most%20commonly%20begins%20in%20young%20adults%20between%20the%20ages%20of%2015%20and%2025%2C%20with%20women%20often%20showing%20symptoms%20slightly%20later%20than%20men.%20Early%20detection%20is%20crucial%2C%20as%20delayed%20diagnosis%20can%20make%20the%20illness%20harder%20to%20manage%20over%20time.%20So%2C%20school%20counsellors%20should%20be%20well%20trained%20and%20alert%20to%20early%20warning%20signs.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22auto%2C%20(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2025%2F05%2Ffeatured-img-54_11zon-1748416077.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22There%20is%20a%20dire%20