3-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Emega-rocket%3C%2Fa%3E%20launched%20from%20its%20Texas%20facility%20on%20Tuesday%20evening%20to%20make%20an%20ill-fated%20third%20attempt%20at%20a%20huge%20milestone%3A%20releasing%20its%20first%20payload%20into%20orbit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20the%20key%20to%20Starship%20bringing%20in%20the%20big%20bucks%20to%20fund%20Musk's%20visions%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-plan-colonize-mars-plan-unrealistic-scientists-explain-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ebuilding%20a%20city%20on%20Mars%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20garner%20paying%20customers%2C%20Starship%20has%20to%20show%20it%20can%20deliver.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20step%20is%20releasing%20a%20batch%20of%20eight%20mock%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Felon-musk-starlink-satellites-internet%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EStarlink%20satellites%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20orbit.%20SpaceX%20tried%20to%20do%20this%20twice%20already%20%E2%80%94%C2%A0in%20January%20and%20March%20%E2%80%94%20only%20to%20see%20Starship%20explode%20before%20it%20could%20even%20try%20opening%20its%20payload%20doors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETuesday's%20flight%20didn't%20fare%20much%20better.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221f68ae3c-fa0f-4899-bc21-00f911570681%5C%22%3E2%20failures%20in%20one%20Starship%20flight%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rocket%20thundered%20through%20the%20skies%20to%20reach%20space%20in%20one%20piece%2C%20but%20when%20it%20came%20time%20to%20release%20its%20practice%20satellites%2C%20the%20payload%20door%20would%20not%20open.%20It's%20not%20yet%20clear%20what%20caused%20that%20first%20mishap.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20hosts%20on%20the%20SpaceX%20livestream%20emphasized%20that%20the%20more%20important%20test%20was%20the%20vehicle's%20reentry%20into%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20because%20SpaceX%20had%20removed%20100%20of%20the%20spaceship's%20protective%20heat-shield%20tiles%20to%20test%20its%20limits.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20l